HEADWORD: Eikon
<hw>Ei"kon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>e'ikw`n</grk>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An image or effigy; -- used
rather in an abstract sense, and rarely for a work of art.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>an ikon.</def>⟦br⟧
